LARGE PROJECT LAYERED CONTEXT ARCHITECTURE:

LAYER STRUCTURE:
1. Foundation Rules (.cursorrules) - Core principles, never changes
2. Project Context (PROJECT_CONTEXT.md) - Architecture, constraints, tech stack
3. Session Context (SESSION_GOALS.md) - Current objectives and blockers
4. Working Memory - Only files currently being modified

SESSION WORKFLOW:
Pre-Session (2 min): Update SESSION_GOALS.md → Review PROJECT_CONTEXT.md → Stage relevant files
During Session: Demand plans before code → Checkpoint every 5-7 exchanges → Use "Explain → Code → Recap"
Post-Session (1 min): Git commit → Update PROJECT_CONTEXT.md → Clear/update SESSION_GOALS.md

CONTEXT OPTIMIZATION:
- Progressive disclosure: Start minimal, add context as needed
- Smart file selection: Core files + feature files + reference files only
- Dynamic context loading with .cursor/context-presets/
- Monitor context degradation, restart after 10+ exchanges without progress
